WEBVTT

00:01.212 --> 00:03.149
‐ You can't tell anyone!
‐ Watch me.

00:03.183 --> 00:04.620
‐ Do you have any idea
what you've done?

00:04.653 --> 00:06.122
Your sister's in the ICU,

00:06.155 --> 00:07.526
a boy is dead,

00:07.559 --> 00:10.430
and our house
is partially destroyed.

00:10.464 --> 00:12.268
‐ Who's gonna believe you?
It's just us.

00:12.301 --> 00:13.804
‐ Life's so short, sweetheart.

00:13.838 --> 00:15.675
I just feel silly to go
on pretending like

00:15.708 --> 00:17.512
everything's okay
when it's not.

00:17.546 --> 00:18.446
‐ Um, how's‐‐how's Junior?

00:18.480 --> 00:20.417
‐ Doctors he can't run
for at least a month

00:20.450 --> 00:22.288
thanks to the damage
to his lungs.

00:22.321 --> 00:24.025
‐ We don't know
how the fire started.

00:24.058 --> 00:26.029
‐ Oliver didn't
die in the fire.

00:26.062 --> 00:27.499
His death has been
ruled a homicide.

00:27.532 --> 00:29.035
All roads lead back to you.

00:29.068 --> 00:31.172
Or more precisely,
to your doll.

00:31.206 --> 00:34.212
‐ You might feel
a little prick.

00:34.245 --> 00:36.784
[grunts]
‐ [screams]

00:36.817 --> 00:40.525
‐ [screaming

00:44.232 --> 00:45.602
‐ Charles Lee Ray
was a serial killer

00:45.635 --> 00:46.469
who died in the eighties.

00:46.503 --> 00:48.674
Supposedly,
right before he died,

00:48.708 --> 00:50.444
he transferred his soul
into a Good Guy doll.

00:50.477 --> 00:52.515
‐ You have to believe me.
Chucky is alive.

00:52.549 --> 00:54.553
He is trying to kill us.

00:54.586 --> 00:57.191
‐ [chuckles]

00:57.224 --> 01:00.130
[upbeat synth music playing]

01:00.163 --> 01:07.244
♪ ♪

01:38.774 --> 01:40.277
‐ Ooh!

01:46.456 --> 01:47.559
‐ Oh.

01:56.376 --> 01:58.446
Oh!

01:58.480 --> 02:00.785
What the‐‐what‐‐

02:00.818 --> 02:02.488
hey, hey, hey.

02:02.522 --> 02:04.893
[grunts]
What the fuck, Delilah?

02:04.926 --> 02:07.364
‐ Oh, come on, don't be
such a pussy, huh?

02:07.398 --> 02:10.772
I said give it to me, now.

02:10.805 --> 02:12.441
‐ Not like that.

02:15.581 --> 02:17.451
‐ Fuck off, Dwayne!

02:31.647 --> 02:33.818
‐ Hi.

02:33.851 --> 02:35.521
Want a smoke?

02:37.391 --> 02:38.694
‐ Thanks.

02:38.728 --> 02:40.130
‐ Well...

02:45.608 --> 02:49.649
It's a shame your friend
had to run off like that.

02:49.683 --> 02:52.187
‐ Maybe that's my problem.

02:52.221 --> 02:54.392
Maybe I'm not looking
for a friend.

02:58.567 --> 03:00.905
‐ Well, maybe
you haven't found one.

03:02.742 --> 03:03.944
‐ Maybe.

03:03.978 --> 03:05.414
Thanks for the light.

03:05.447 --> 03:09.288
‐ Hey, where are you going?

03:12.696 --> 03:16.670
‐ I'm looking for something
very specific.

03:16.704 --> 03:18.708
‐ [chuckles]

03:18.741 --> 03:20.243
Try me.

03:22.414 --> 03:24.553
‐ You guys are all the same.

03:24.586 --> 03:28.961
‐ I promise you,
I'm not like anybody else.

03:32.401 --> 03:35.407
[machinery beeping]

03:35.440 --> 03:38.547
[apprehensive music]

03:38.581 --> 03:45.460
♪ ♪

03:47.899 --> 03:51.840
‐ Caroline, Caroline.

03:51.874 --> 03:54.245
‐ I like to be hugged.

03:58.821 --> 04:00.525
Where's Chucky?

04:00.558 --> 04:02.896
‐ Oh, sweetie,
Chucky's had a few boo‐boos

04:02.929 --> 04:04.265
and needs to rest up.

04:04.298 --> 04:05.668
Maybe you could see him
in a little bit.

04:05.701 --> 04:07.304
‐ I want Chucky.

04:07.337 --> 04:09.341
I want Chucky.

04:09.375 --> 04:10.912
I want Chucky!

04:10.945 --> 04:17.291
‐ Okay, but Chucky looks
a little different now, honey.

04:21.934 --> 04:25.575
‐ [screaming]

04:34.058 --> 04:37.331
‐ [shouts]

04:43.777 --> 04:45.781
Ah.

04:45.815 --> 04:48.754
[mumbling]

04:50.892 --> 04:54.933
[laughing]

04:54.966 --> 04:57.939
Ah, what a fucking rush!

04:57.972 --> 04:59.041
That's the good shit.

04:59.074 --> 05:02.347
[laughing]

05:09.963 --> 05:11.900
God, I love hospitals.

05:11.934 --> 05:14.873
[playful spooky music]

05:14.906 --> 05:21.820
♪ ♪

05:31.372 --> 05:33.978
‐ Oh, my baby!

05:34.011 --> 05:35.882
Look at you!

05:35.915 --> 05:38.086
Excuse me.
‐ Mm.

05:38.119 --> 05:40.958
‐ Oh, sweet pea.

05:40.992 --> 05:46.002
‐ Hey Care, um,
where's Chucky?

05:46.035 --> 05:48.006
I was thinking
maybe I could take him

05:48.039 --> 05:50.811
to go get a Snickers
or something.

05:50.845 --> 05:54.719
He must be starving after
taking such good care of you.

05:54.753 --> 05:58.694
‐ I hate Chucky.
I hate Chucky! He's bad.

05:58.727 --> 05:59.863
‐ Jesus, Lexy.

05:59.896 --> 06:03.604
It's all daisies
until you dampen the mood.

06:03.637 --> 06:05.106
‐ I was just trying to help.

06:05.140 --> 06:07.444
‐ Your mother and I both know

06:07.477 --> 06:08.514
that you want
what's best for Caroline.

06:08.547 --> 06:11.018
‐ I don't know that.

06:11.052 --> 06:13.524
I don't.

06:13.557 --> 06:15.393
‐ But Caroline's decided that

06:15.427 --> 06:17.565
she doesn't like
Chucky anymore,

06:17.599 --> 06:19.168
so we took care of it.

06:19.201 --> 06:20.905
I threw him in the garbage.

06:20.938 --> 06:23.877
[suspenseful music]

06:23.911 --> 06:28.453
♪ ♪

06:28.486 --> 06:30.423
‐ Follow me.

06:34.064 --> 06:35.433
This way.

06:45.721 --> 06:47.659
[metallic crash]

06:51.600 --> 06:52.568
Come on.

07:04.258 --> 07:06.663
What are the chances
he burned to death?

07:09.669 --> 07:10.605
Okay.

07:22.895 --> 07:23.864
Ah.

07:23.897 --> 07:30.811
♪ ♪

07:38.092 --> 07:39.596
Uh‐uh.

07:39.629 --> 07:42.067
No way, this is disgusting.

07:42.100 --> 07:44.739
‐ We have to be sure.

07:44.773 --> 07:46.510
‐ I don't know what's worse,
stabbed with a butcher knife

07:46.543 --> 07:49.114
or a used needle.

07:49.148 --> 07:52.655
‐ I'll do it. It's my mess.

07:54.926 --> 07:56.897
‐ We're in this together.

07:56.930 --> 08:00.070
‐ Together.
‐ That's what I said.

08:00.103 --> 08:01.973
[machinery churns]

08:03.309 --> 08:04.946
‐ Maybe we‐‐you know,

08:04.979 --> 08:06.616
we could wait for him
to come for us.

08:06.650 --> 08:08.821
He can't stay
down there forever.

08:08.854 --> 08:09.689
‐ He can't?

08:09.723 --> 08:10.725
What exactly are the rules

08:10.758 --> 08:12.695
for supernaturally
possessed dolls?

08:12.729 --> 08:15.033
‐ Hey, guys, I have an idea.

08:15.066 --> 08:16.937
I'll get him out.

08:21.813 --> 08:23.917
‐ Lexy, dig.

08:25.186 --> 08:29.028
Devon, keep watch.

08:29.061 --> 08:30.998
‐ Uh‐uh. No, absolutely not.

08:31.032 --> 08:33.169
There's like seven diseases
down there.

08:33.202 --> 08:36.175
‐ Did you not just say
"together"?

08:36.208 --> 08:40.183
‐ You do it.
‐ Fine by me.

08:40.216 --> 08:43.156
Ready to take him down
if he jumps out?

08:43.189 --> 08:45.226
‐ Ugh, fine.

08:48.066 --> 08:49.736
‐ Just follow my lead.

08:55.313 --> 08:57.250
Oh, shit.

09:00.591 --> 09:02.995
Three, two, one.

09:03.029 --> 09:05.333
Go!

09:05.366 --> 09:06.636
‐ Over there.

09:08.339 --> 09:10.076
Jake, over there.

09:10.110 --> 09:11.646
‐ Eat this, Chucky!

09:27.612 --> 09:31.920
‐ Ugh, so gross!

09:31.953 --> 09:38.901
♪ ♪

09:51.225 --> 09:55.968
‐ A few days ago, you were
probably feeling shock, denial.

09:56.001 --> 09:56.803
That's normal.

09:56.837 --> 09:59.976
All of this is
so much to take in.

10:00.009 --> 10:03.984
At this point, you might be
feeling pain and guilt.

10:09.161 --> 10:11.031
That's still normal.

10:11.065 --> 10:13.804
Your feelings are valid
and expected.

10:13.837 --> 10:15.808
Everyone will heal
at their own speed,

10:15.841 --> 10:19.014
and if you need
anyone to talk to,

10:19.047 --> 10:21.987
please know my door
is always open to you guys.

10:23.322 --> 10:26.095
I, know, probably think
I'm just the biology teacher,

10:26.128 --> 10:29.903
but feelings do start
on the molecular level.

10:29.936 --> 10:32.742
Okay, let's pick back up
where we left off.

10:32.775 --> 10:35.748
Chapter Three:
Biotic and Abiotic Factors.

10:35.781 --> 10:38.286
What are living and non‐living
beings of life?

10:38.319 --> 10:39.956
[knock at door]

10:45.266 --> 10:47.304
[inquisitive music]

10:47.337 --> 10:49.809
Why don't you guys get started
on the chapter questions.

10:49.843 --> 10:51.412
I'll be back in just a minute.

10:51.445 --> 10:58.861
♪ ♪

10:59.428 --> 11:01.800
‐ How does he even
move around so fast?

11:01.833 --> 11:03.302
He's a freaking doll.

11:03.336 --> 11:05.273
‐ Maybe he left Hackensack.
‐ No.

11:05.306 --> 11:07.712
He's a psycho back
in his hometown on a mission.

11:07.745 --> 11:09.047
He's not leaving.

11:11.252 --> 11:13.122
‐ What do we do about Junior?

11:16.262 --> 11:18.332
‐ We should tell him.

11:18.366 --> 11:19.702
‐ No.

11:19.736 --> 11:21.706
No, we can't
bring him into this.

11:21.740 --> 11:23.409
He doesn't have
the imagination.

11:26.382 --> 11:28.352
It's just the three of us.

11:28.386 --> 11:31.058
‐ Guys, we have to think.

11:31.091 --> 11:32.962
No one's reported any
weird shit since the hospital

11:32.995 --> 11:35.768
so he must be itching
to kill by now.

11:35.801 --> 11:37.939
‐ Maybe we're going about this
the wrong way.

11:37.972 --> 11:40.443
Maybe it's not where
he's going next, its...

11:40.476 --> 11:43.115
‐ It's who.

11:43.149 --> 11:44.852
Devon,

11:44.886 --> 11:46.355
you know serial killers
better than anyone.

11:46.388 --> 11:48.727
What are you thinking?

11:48.760 --> 11:50.931
‐ Well, most of the time
it's opportunity,

11:50.965 --> 11:53.135
but sometimes they fixate
on a certain kind‐‐

11:53.169 --> 11:55.206
‐ What're you guys
talking about?

11:55.240 --> 11:55.941
‐ Nothing.

11:59.014 --> 12:01.051
‐ Have you guys seen
"Westworld?"

12:01.085 --> 12:03.957
It's a crazy theme park
with these hot robots

12:03.991 --> 12:05.460
and you can, like,
do anything you want to them.

12:05.494 --> 12:08.967
It's really cool.

12:09.001 --> 12:12.040
‐ I haven't.
Been a little busy.

12:14.512 --> 12:16.783
‐ Haven't really had time
for that this week.

12:21.258 --> 12:25.133
‐ Guys, can we get
back to work please?

12:25.166 --> 12:27.805
Less chat, more science.

12:29.241 --> 12:30.978
All right,
who can give me an example

12:31.011 --> 12:33.282
of one of the biotic factors?

12:33.316 --> 12:34.519
Lexy?

12:34.552 --> 12:36.155
[phone buzzes]

12:36.188 --> 12:37.758
Biotic factors? No?

12:39.328 --> 12:40.764
[bell rings]

12:41.933 --> 12:44.404
‐ Devon, this is all my fault.

12:44.438 --> 12:47.210
Oliver would still be alive
if it wasn't for me.

12:47.243 --> 12:50.049
[solemn music]

12:50.083 --> 12:52.955
‐ Pain's a lot easier if you
let someone feel it with you.

12:58.366 --> 13:00.203
Hey.

13:00.236 --> 13:02.073
Close your eyes.

13:02.107 --> 13:04.144
‐ What?
‐ Just do it.

13:06.181 --> 13:07.183
‐ Okay.

13:09.087 --> 13:12.260
‐ Now, think of
everything you're feeling,

13:12.294 --> 13:14.264
deep in your gut.

13:14.298 --> 13:15.934
Unfiltered.

13:17.470 --> 13:20.009
[soft exciting music]

13:20.043 --> 13:22.515
‐ You ever have those dreams
where you're running in place?

13:26.990 --> 13:29.529
It feels like I'm running,
just like that.

13:31.365 --> 13:34.539
The world is crashing down
because of something I did.

13:36.342 --> 13:39.949
But I can't run to fix it.

13:39.982 --> 13:41.586
Can't run from it.

13:41.619 --> 13:45.293
Just stuck somewhere
in the middle,

13:45.326 --> 13:47.898
watching it all burn down.

13:47.932 --> 13:50.370
There's nothing I can do
but pump my arms faster.

13:50.403 --> 13:57.283
♪ ♪

14:09.107 --> 14:12.180
[rapid indistinct chatter]

14:26.976 --> 14:31.118
‐ Oh.
All right,
this smell is disgusting.

14:31.151 --> 14:33.957
‐ Don't worry, Marta's
is gonna make this dump

14:33.990 --> 14:36.663
camera ready again in time
for the New Year's Eve ball.

14:36.696 --> 14:38.365
‐ How much is that
gonna cost us?

14:38.399 --> 14:39.569
‐ Nothing.

14:39.602 --> 14:41.371
It's on the good people
of Hackensack.

14:41.405 --> 14:43.677
‐ How are the people gonna feel
about their tax dollars

14:43.710 --> 14:45.480
paying to clean up our mess?

14:45.514 --> 14:48.385
‐ They'll be happy
to help restore order

14:48.419 --> 14:51.158
and grateful for
the sense of security.

14:51.191 --> 14:54.097
The people of this town
need to know they're safe.

14:54.131 --> 14:56.101
And the town hall tonight

14:56.135 --> 14:58.607
will be the perfect way
to convince them.

14:58.640 --> 15:00.376
‐ You mean "reach them."

15:00.410 --> 15:03.082
‐ You mean "lie to them."

15:03.115 --> 15:04.685
‐ Excuse me?

15:04.719 --> 15:07.525
‐ Whatever.
I gotta get outta here.

15:07.558 --> 15:09.695
‐ I don't think so.

15:09.729 --> 15:11.165
You're grounded.

15:12.735 --> 15:14.070
‐ What?

15:14.104 --> 15:16.543
‐ You caused all this.
You have to live in it with us.

15:16.576 --> 15:19.114
You're grounded
until I say you're not.

15:22.454 --> 15:24.424
Where are you going?

15:24.458 --> 15:26.061
Uh‐uh.

15:26.095 --> 15:29.367
[tense music]

15:29.401 --> 15:31.405
Exactly.

15:31.438 --> 15:33.242
‐ Honey.
‐ Ugh.

15:33.275 --> 15:35.413
I won't with her anymore.

15:35.446 --> 15:37.985
Every time she speaks,
it's cheap silver

15:38.018 --> 15:39.421
on a mass produced
dinner plate.

15:39.454 --> 15:41.693
‐ Show her some compassion.

15:41.726 --> 15:44.097
You know, maybe get through to
her a little more effectively.

15:44.131 --> 15:46.970
‐ She nearly burned the
whole damn house down, Nathan.

15:47.003 --> 15:49.307
I'm running a little low
on compassion at the moment.

15:49.341 --> 15:51.378
‐ Which I understand, but look,

15:51.411 --> 15:53.382
do we care more
about how our life looks

15:53.415 --> 15:54.685
or how it feels?

15:54.719 --> 15:58.392
You know, Lexy's hurting too.

15:58.425 --> 16:00.229
‐ Touchy‐feely Nathan

16:00.263 --> 16:03.670
is my least favorite Nathan,
just so you know.

16:05.173 --> 16:06.576
‐ How cool would it be

16:06.609 --> 16:10.082
if you got to sleep down here
in Mommy's office?

16:10.116 --> 16:12.555
‐ There's no bed.
‐ Well, it's a sofa bed.

16:12.588 --> 16:14.024
Nana slept here, remember?

16:14.057 --> 16:17.397
‐ Nana's dead.
‐ Well, now.

16:17.430 --> 16:20.136
Yeah, but she didn't‐‐

16:20.169 --> 16:23.242
hey, look.

16:23.275 --> 16:24.612
What do you think of that, huh?

16:24.645 --> 16:26.716
‐ I want my bed, I want my bed.

16:26.749 --> 16:28.587
I want my bed!
‐ Honey! Honey, honey.

16:28.620 --> 16:30.691
Guess what? Guess what?

16:30.724 --> 16:32.427
I have a surprise for you.

16:32.460 --> 16:34.565
Close your eyes.

16:41.513 --> 16:43.650
Open 'em.

16:43.683 --> 16:45.754
‐ Where did that come from?

16:45.787 --> 16:49.194
‐ Hi, I'm Tommy.
Wanna play?

16:49.227 --> 16:51.431
‐ Dad, where did you get that?
‐ I got it online.

16:51.465 --> 16:55.306
‐ From who?
‐ "From whom."

16:55.339 --> 16:56.643
‐ I like to be hugged.

16:56.676 --> 16:58.713
[unsettling music]

16:58.747 --> 17:01.786
‐ Tommy hugs too,
just like Chucky.

17:01.819 --> 17:03.823
‐ Oh.

17:03.857 --> 17:05.059
Hey, Care,

17:05.092 --> 17:08.232
do you think that Tommy
would give me a hug too?

17:08.265 --> 17:15.213
♪ ♪

17:16.683 --> 17:18.485
‐ [breathing heavily]

17:18.520 --> 17:20.524
‐ Lexy!
Sweetie, what are you doing?

17:20.557 --> 17:23.128
‐ Stop hurting him. Stop!
‐ Stop it!

17:23.162 --> 17:24.464
Do something!

17:24.498 --> 17:26.268
Lexy, stop it right now!

17:26.301 --> 17:28.405
Stop it.
‐ Stop!

17:28.439 --> 17:31.512
‐ [panting]

17:33.550 --> 17:36.355
[camera clicks]

17:36.388 --> 17:37.691
‐ Uh...

17:37.725 --> 17:40.764
[thunder crashes]

17:48.880 --> 17:50.651
‐ So I have some good news.

17:50.684 --> 17:53.723
‐ You do?
[thunder rumbles]

17:53.757 --> 17:55.527
‐ I made a few phone calls.

17:57.330 --> 18:00.102
Thanks to a favor owed,

18:00.136 --> 18:03.142
Junior, you're still going
to nationals next month.

18:09.421 --> 18:10.489
‐ Is that really the best idea?

18:10.524 --> 18:12.126
The doctor did say
that Junior was‐‐

18:12.160 --> 18:15.567
‐ I missed regionals
'cause I was in the hospital.

18:15.601 --> 18:18.573
I didn't qualify for nationals.

18:18.607 --> 18:21.478
Isn't that kind of unfair?

18:21.512 --> 18:24.217
[thunder rumbles]

18:24.250 --> 18:26.689
‐ Let this be
a teaching moment, kid.

18:26.723 --> 18:28.827
In life,
when you get advantages,

18:28.860 --> 18:31.532
you have to take 'em.

18:31.566 --> 18:32.501
So in a week or two,
you're gonna‐‐

18:32.534 --> 18:34.137
[phone buzzes]

18:36.274 --> 18:37.544
In a week or two,
we're gonna have you

18:37.578 --> 18:39.782
back out there running.

18:39.815 --> 18:41.753
I even got you a trainer.

18:41.786 --> 18:44.859
That guy, Dobbs. He's the best.

18:49.434 --> 18:50.837
That's okay, right?

18:52.440 --> 18:54.144
‐ Logan‐‐
[phone buzzes]

18:54.177 --> 18:56.281
Jake, please,
no phones at the dinner table.

19:01.926 --> 19:04.230
‐ What's she doing texting you?

19:04.264 --> 19:05.534
She hasn't returned
my texts all day.

19:05.567 --> 19:07.905
‐ Okay. Phone, now.

19:07.938 --> 19:11.178
‐ Sorry, I‐‐I can't do that.

19:11.211 --> 19:12.781
‐ You can have it back
after dinner.

19:12.815 --> 19:14.552
[phone buzzes]

19:14.585 --> 19:18.459
‐ Yeah, hand over
the phone, Jake.

19:18.493 --> 19:21.365
‐ No.
‐ [scoffs]

19:21.398 --> 19:22.467
‐ Boys.

19:22.501 --> 19:23.570
‐ What are you doing?

19:23.603 --> 19:25.306
‐ Give me the phone,
you assbag!

19:25.339 --> 19:26.475
‐ Boys, seriously!

19:26.509 --> 19:27.644
‐ Hey!

19:27.678 --> 19:29.381
Drop it.

19:29.414 --> 19:32.387
[tense music]

19:32.420 --> 19:39.367
♪ ♪

19:51.726 --> 19:52.895
You give 'em everything
and at the end,

19:52.928 --> 19:55.232
all you can do is
hope for the best.

19:56.936 --> 19:58.907
‐ Logan,
I think we need to talk.

20:01.411 --> 20:03.382
‐ About?

20:03.415 --> 20:04.819
‐ Just‐‐

20:07.490 --> 20:08.960
Maybe now is not the best time

20:08.993 --> 20:12.501
to have an extra son
in the house.

20:12.534 --> 20:14.471
I just feel like everything
is falling to pieces

20:14.505 --> 20:16.374
and I'm not entirely sure
that what you're doing

20:16.408 --> 20:17.711
is helpful.

20:20.049 --> 20:23.923
‐ I'm not my brother, Bree.

20:23.957 --> 20:26.529
‐ That's not what I mean.

20:26.562 --> 20:27.931
‐ Then what did you mean?

20:34.745 --> 20:36.949
Oh, what was I saying before?

20:36.983 --> 20:39.989
[indistinct conversation]

20:46.502 --> 20:49.642
[thunder rumbles]

20:50.510 --> 20:54.718
‐ ♪ The itsy bitsy spider
crawled up the water spout ♪

20:54.752 --> 20:58.726
♪ Out came the rain
and washed the spider out ♪

20:58.760 --> 21:02.467
♪ Out came the sun
and dried up all the rain ♪

21:02.501 --> 21:07.343
♪ And the itsy bitsy spider
crawled up the spout again ♪

21:07.376 --> 21:10.349
[eerie music]

21:10.382 --> 21:17.330
♪ ♪

21:41.979 --> 21:49.294
[eerie music] ♪ ♪

21:58.980 --> 22:03.690
‐ Start. What the‐‐?

22:03.723 --> 22:06.829
Tried‐‐so, okay.
‐ Move.

22:09.935 --> 22:13.810
[dishwasher humming]

22:13.843 --> 22:14.979
‐ Oh.
‐ What the hell?

22:15.012 --> 22:15.981
Where did that come from?

22:16.014 --> 22:17.584
‐ Lexy, this isn't funny.

22:17.618 --> 22:20.991
Hasn't your sister
been through enough?

22:21.024 --> 22:22.828
‐ No, that's not fair.
There's no way‐‐

22:22.861 --> 22:23.963
‐ Michelle,
it's not a big deal.

22:23.997 --> 22:25.534
I was just gonna throw it out.

22:25.567 --> 22:26.602
‐ Please do.

22:26.636 --> 22:28.940
And Lexy, now just‐‐

22:28.973 --> 22:30.944
just get outta my sight.
Go to your room.

22:30.977 --> 22:33.048
‐ She doesn't have
a room anymore, remember?

22:33.081 --> 22:34.718
‐ And whose fault is that?

22:34.752 --> 22:38.025
‐ Jesus, Michelle,
would you just give it a rest?

22:39.728 --> 22:41.097
[door slams]

22:41.131 --> 22:44.003
‐ Okay, so I'm
the bad guy here.

22:44.037 --> 22:51.351
♪ ♪

23:08.018 --> 23:09.454
‐ What are you thinking, Jake?

23:09.487 --> 23:11.626
‐ I figure we kick his ass
till he's dead.

23:11.659 --> 23:12.594
‐ Hell yeah!

23:18.773 --> 23:20.610
‐ Nathan,

23:20.644 --> 23:22.648
don't ever
undermine my authority

23:22.681 --> 23:23.950
in front of the kids.

23:23.983 --> 23:25.754
We talked about this.
It's hard enough‐‐

23:25.787 --> 23:27.658
‐ Pick a lane, Michelle.

23:27.691 --> 23:28.760
‐ I despise sports metaphors.

23:28.793 --> 23:31.431
‐ Pick a lane.

23:31.464 --> 23:32.734
‐ Talk to me like a grownup.

23:32.768 --> 23:34.638
A man, for example.

23:34.672 --> 23:36.107
‐ All right. Mom or mayor.

23:36.141 --> 23:37.611
‐ Excuse me?
‐ Choose.

23:37.644 --> 23:39.480
Because I'm not so sure
you can do both anymore.

23:39.515 --> 23:40.884
‐ Oh, that's crazy
and you know it.

23:40.917 --> 23:43.021
‐ Oh, is it?
‐ It's also impossible.

23:43.055 --> 23:44.591
‐ Lexy didn't sign up for this,

23:44.625 --> 23:45.727
and neither did I.

23:45.760 --> 23:46.896
‐ How about mom and mayor?

23:46.929 --> 23:48.031
Did you think of that?

23:48.065 --> 23:49.768
Because that's the best
I can do,

23:49.802 --> 23:53.509
and I do it pretty damn well
if you ask me.

23:53.543 --> 23:55.647
Nathan?

23:55.680 --> 23:57.517
Nathan!

24:01.592 --> 24:05.466
[clattering]

24:05.500 --> 24:06.802
‐ Stay.

24:06.836 --> 24:07.971
[clattering]

24:08.005 --> 24:10.744
Sh‐‐okay.

24:10.777 --> 24:14.250
Oh, shit!

24:14.283 --> 24:16.689
[clattering]
Hey, okay.

24:16.722 --> 24:17.824
Okay.
‐ Hey.

24:17.858 --> 24:20.797
‐ Um, get‐‐get the sack.
‐ Okay.

24:20.830 --> 24:23.201
Mm, okay.
‐ Shit.

24:23.235 --> 24:24.805
‐ Are you sure
this is gonna work?

24:24.838 --> 24:27.944
‐ No.
‐ Are you serious right now?

24:27.978 --> 24:29.047
What do you mean, no?
‐ It'll work.

24:29.080 --> 24:31.686
It has to, right?

24:31.719 --> 24:34.090
‐ Okay. All right, ready?

24:34.123 --> 24:37.263
Three, two, one.

24:37.296 --> 24:38.833
‐ [hissing]
[all shout]

24:38.866 --> 24:40.937
‐ [gasps]

24:42.841 --> 24:44.043
Okay!

24:44.077 --> 24:47.116
[hard rock music]

24:47.149 --> 24:50.590
‐ I like‐‐I like‐‐
I like to be hugged.

24:50.623 --> 24:52.059
‐ Get him in!

24:52.093 --> 24:54.832
♪ ♪

24:54.865 --> 24:56.234
‐ Yeah!

24:56.267 --> 24:59.708
‐ I like to be hugged.

24:59.742 --> 25:02.714
[voice stuttering]
I like to be hugged.

25:02.748 --> 25:04.117
[sound falters, fades]

25:04.150 --> 25:07.858
‐ Okay.
‐ [breathing heavily]

25:07.891 --> 25:09.728
[clattering]

25:09.762 --> 25:11.197
Oh, my God.

25:11.231 --> 25:13.101
The little fucker's dead!

25:13.135 --> 25:17.711
Oh, yeah!
[laughs]

25:17.744 --> 25:19.815
Yes!
‐ [chuckles]

25:19.848 --> 25:22.153
‐ Holy shit!

25:22.186 --> 25:23.689
‐ What about
Caroline's new doll?

25:23.723 --> 25:24.357
What about Tommy?

25:24.390 --> 25:26.094
‐ No, I checked. Totally cool.

25:26.127 --> 25:27.564
Tommy's just a dumb doll.

25:29.300 --> 25:33.008
Take the win, Jake.
Chucky is dead!

25:33.041 --> 25:35.880
[Lauv's "Modern Loneliness"]

25:35.914 --> 25:38.151
♪ ♪

25:38.185 --> 25:39.888
‐ Hey, man, hurry,
the sun's coming up.

25:39.922 --> 25:40.890
‐ Okay.

25:40.924 --> 25:43.896
[both chuckling]

25:43.930 --> 25:47.336
♪ ♪

25:47.369 --> 25:51.311
‐ ♪ I've been thinking
'bout my father lately ♪

25:51.344 --> 25:54.016
♪ The person that he made me ♪

25:54.050 --> 25:56.655
‐ We did it.

25:56.689 --> 26:00.630
‐ Yeah, Chucky's gone.
He's really gone.

26:00.663 --> 26:02.534
‐ Kicked his ass
just like you said.

26:07.076 --> 26:09.782
‐ What do we do now?

26:09.815 --> 26:12.788
‐ I don't know.
Go back to normal, I guess.

26:12.821 --> 26:14.190
‐ Right.

26:14.223 --> 26:18.599
Except that‐‐
‐ Except what?

26:18.633 --> 26:22.106
‐ Sometimes I'm not sure
what normal feels like anymore.

26:22.139 --> 26:24.778
‐ I feel like that
all the time.

26:24.812 --> 26:25.780
‐ You do?

26:28.653 --> 26:30.890
What are you thinking, Devon?

26:30.924 --> 26:32.126
‐ I'm thinking...

26:34.097 --> 26:36.936
This is a problem
we can solve together.

26:36.969 --> 26:38.706
‐ Okay.

26:38.739 --> 26:43.816
‐ ♪ The baggage in my heart
is still so dark ♪

26:45.987 --> 26:48.726
‐ [chuckles]

26:48.759 --> 26:54.270
♪ ♪

26:54.303 --> 26:58.111
[both chuckle]

26:58.145 --> 27:00.817
‐ [laughs]

27:00.850 --> 27:02.787
‐ Bye, Jake.

27:02.821 --> 27:05.827
‐ See you, Devon.

27:05.860 --> 27:07.964
‐ ♪ La, di, da, di, da, yeah ♪

27:07.998 --> 27:11.705
♪ You get what you give
and you give what you get ♪

27:11.739 --> 27:13.976
♪ Modern loneliness ♪

27:14.010 --> 27:14.945
♪ We love to get high ♪

27:14.978 --> 27:16.381
♪ But we don't know
how to come down ♪

27:24.096 --> 27:26.902
[upbeat pop music playing] ♪ ♪

27:26.936 --> 27:29.775
‐ See anything you like?

27:29.808 --> 27:32.213
‐ As a matter of fact, I do.

27:32.246 --> 27:37.256
♪ ♪

27:37.289 --> 27:39.795
Hey, Red, what's new?

27:43.803 --> 27:46.876
‐ Is there something
I can do for you?

27:46.909 --> 27:50.215
[unsettling music]

27:50.249 --> 27:52.787
‐ Yeah, maybe there is.

27:52.821 --> 27:55.760
[Modern Art's
"Hello / Goodbye"]

27:55.793 --> 28:02.741
♪ ♪

28:04.110 --> 28:07.049
‐ [chuckles]

28:07.082 --> 28:10.188
[both sighing]

28:20.242 --> 28:23.950
[necklace snaps]
‐ Ah! [laughs]

28:23.983 --> 28:25.720
[metal scrapes]

28:25.753 --> 28:28.258
‐ ♪ I walk back
into your life ♪

28:28.291 --> 28:34.270
♪ ♪

28:34.303 --> 28:38.178
♪ You ask me
where I've been to ♪

28:40.550 --> 28:43.021
‐ Hey.

28:43.054 --> 28:46.160
‐ ♪ I don't know what to say ♪

28:50.135 --> 28:51.471
‐ Do it.

28:55.980 --> 28:58.051
Do it to me, now.

28:58.084 --> 29:05.198
♪ ♪

29:12.179 --> 29:14.851
‐ Charles, what the hell?

29:14.885 --> 29:16.822
Hello! What the hell?

29:19.126 --> 29:21.966
‐ [grunting]

29:21.999 --> 29:23.234
‐ [gasping]

29:23.268 --> 29:25.773
‐ Hey, Red, wanna play?

29:25.807 --> 29:28.512
‐ [gasping]

29:28.546 --> 29:31.084
‐ [chuckles]

29:31.117 --> 29:34.156
[grunting]

29:38.231 --> 29:41.538
[crying out]

29:41.572 --> 29:44.477
[laughs]

29:48.318 --> 29:51.892
Wow, it's never happened
like that before.

29:51.925 --> 29:53.996
[chuckles]

29:54.030 --> 29:55.132
Is that me?

29:55.165 --> 29:58.438
‐ Oh, it's definitely you.

30:01.044 --> 30:03.949
[both moaning]

30:08.058 --> 30:10.563
‐ [chuckles]

30:10.596 --> 30:13.301
Boy, you really know
how to show a girl a good time.

30:13.335 --> 30:15.840
[both chuckle]

30:15.873 --> 30:17.343
I'm Tiffany.

30:17.376 --> 30:19.447
‐ I'm Charles.

30:19.480 --> 30:21.919
‐ Know what, Charles?

30:21.952 --> 30:23.889
You should be Chucky.

30:25.225 --> 30:27.062
‐ You know what, Tiff?

30:27.096 --> 30:28.933
You should be blonde.

30:38.251 --> 30:41.491
‐ My secret.
It's all I think about.

30:43.562 --> 30:46.034
I know it's wrong,
of course it is.

30:50.008 --> 30:51.411
I think about Logan

30:51.444 --> 30:54.216
and the look on his face
when I finally say the words.

30:56.120 --> 30:58.358
Every time I try to tell him
I just can't.

30:59.961 --> 31:02.967
But I don't think I can
keep this a secret anymore.

31:03.001 --> 31:06.207
‐ Have you thought about
telling Junior first?

31:06.240 --> 31:09.146
‐ Junior is just a boy.

31:09.180 --> 31:11.317
He'll find out soon enough.

31:11.350 --> 31:13.354
Besides, with Jake
coming to live with us,

31:13.388 --> 31:16.662
he's been through a lot,
you know?

31:16.695 --> 31:18.999
And as if Logan
doesn't put enough pressure

31:19.033 --> 31:20.368
on Junior as it is.

31:20.402 --> 31:21.605
He just won't let up.

31:21.638 --> 31:23.642
Did you know that last night‐‐
‐ Bree.

31:26.013 --> 31:27.650
Your illness?

31:31.057 --> 31:33.395
‐ Stage four cancer.

31:35.700 --> 31:38.973
[contemplative piano music]

31:39.006 --> 31:42.647
♪ ♪

31:42.680 --> 31:46.020
You know, I say the words
and it still doesn't feel real.

31:50.696 --> 31:53.602
I just wanted to protect
everyone for as long as I could

31:53.636 --> 31:58.979
so I made a decision;
I didn't tell them.

31:59.013 --> 32:01.317
‐ You spared them.

32:01.350 --> 32:02.654
You took all that weight

32:02.687 --> 32:04.423
and put it on your shoulders.

32:04.457 --> 32:06.260
How does that feel?

32:06.294 --> 32:07.997
‐ Lonely.

32:08.031 --> 32:10.168
‐ No wonder.

32:10.202 --> 32:12.607
‐ I have to tell them.

32:12.640 --> 32:14.611
I will.

32:14.644 --> 32:16.481
I don't want
to go through this alone.

32:18.986 --> 32:20.288
No matter
how I treat my illness

32:20.322 --> 32:23.294
or what's going on at home.

32:23.328 --> 32:24.263
‐ Bree...

32:26.635 --> 32:30.041
Let the people you love
back into your life.

32:31.444 --> 32:32.981
‐ Yeah.

32:40.462 --> 32:43.434
[eerie music]

32:43.468 --> 32:50.482
♪ ♪

32:51.484 --> 32:54.558
[both groaning]

33:06.113 --> 33:09.053
‐ [chuckles]

33:10.590 --> 33:12.760
‐ What's the matter,
little fella?

33:12.794 --> 33:16.602
Are you not enjoying the show?

33:16.635 --> 33:19.473
‐ [muffled groaning]

33:19.508 --> 33:20.776
‐ What about that, Chucky?

33:20.810 --> 33:23.481
We put on a really nice show
for this young man

33:23.516 --> 33:26.454
and all he does is
moan and complain.

33:30.395 --> 33:32.366
What do you want, little fella?

33:32.399 --> 33:35.372
[blows puff of air, chuckles]

33:35.405 --> 33:40.282
Mmm, I need a snack.

33:40.315 --> 33:44.390
‐ Yeah, does look kinda yummy.

33:44.423 --> 33:47.630
‐ I'm thrilled you've expanded
your palette, Chucky,

33:47.664 --> 33:49.634
but I was talking about

33:49.668 --> 33:55.646
a real snack,
like Swedish meatballs.

33:55.680 --> 33:57.249
‐ Wait, you're hungry?

33:57.282 --> 33:58.619
‐ Yeah.
‐ Now?

33:58.652 --> 34:01.123
‐ Yeah, I'm hungry.
I wanna eat something.

34:01.157 --> 34:03.428
‐ Jesus Christ,
you're always hungry.

34:03.461 --> 34:04.798
‐ Yeah, I'm always hungry.

34:04.831 --> 34:06.467
‐ You know, I'd say you were
turning into your mother,

34:06.501 --> 34:07.770
but that would be
an improvement.

34:07.804 --> 34:11.410
‐ You know, my mother
always told me,

34:11.444 --> 34:13.549
"Never let a man cockblock you

34:13.582 --> 34:15.686
from what really
makes you happy."

34:15.720 --> 34:18.726
And eating makes me happy!

34:18.759 --> 34:21.798
‐ Go get fat then!
‐ Maybe I will.

34:21.832 --> 34:23.569
‐ Go!

34:27.610 --> 34:28.712
[metal scrapes]

34:28.746 --> 34:30.816
[sighs]

34:30.850 --> 34:34.423
You know, if killing with Tiff

34:34.456 --> 34:36.695
is the best time
I ever had in my life,

34:36.728 --> 34:38.197
how come I feel like

34:38.231 --> 34:41.872
strangling her
with my own bare hands?

34:41.905 --> 34:43.542
Huh?

34:47.650 --> 34:49.554
You wanna know why?

34:51.357 --> 34:52.860
Because love...

34:55.198 --> 34:56.300
Is strange.

34:56.334 --> 34:59.774
‐ [groans]
‐ [chuckles]

35:02.379 --> 35:06.220
[eerie music]

35:06.253 --> 35:08.324
[cries out]

35:08.358 --> 35:11.531
[groans]

35:11.565 --> 35:15.205
Oh, what?

35:17.275 --> 35:19.446
Where am I?

35:19.480 --> 35:22.452
Oh! Oh, my God.

35:22.486 --> 35:25.225
Are you okay?

35:25.258 --> 35:27.162
[grunts]

35:27.195 --> 35:30.335
I'm sorry, my legs‐‐
I'm paraplegic.

35:30.368 --> 35:32.205
‐ [gasps]

35:32.239 --> 35:34.209
Please don't kill me,
please don't kill me.

35:34.243 --> 35:35.078
‐ What?

35:38.284 --> 35:41.190
Oh, my God.

35:41.223 --> 35:42.627
What day is today?

35:42.660 --> 35:44.764
‐ What?
‐ What is the date?

35:44.798 --> 35:47.770
‐ November 8th, I guess?
I don't know.

35:47.804 --> 35:50.241
‐ It's been two weeks.
‐ Please don't kill me.

35:52.412 --> 35:53.916
‐ No, no, no, no.

35:53.949 --> 35:56.788
I'm not a killer.
You don't understand.

35:56.822 --> 35:59.393
‐ Are you fucking serious
right now?

35:59.426 --> 36:00.830
I watched you murder him!

36:03.401 --> 36:06.541
‐ [sobs]
No!

36:06.575 --> 36:08.444
Look, you don't understand.

36:08.478 --> 36:11.551
My name is Nica Pierce and‐‐

36:14.423 --> 36:15.826
Oh, no.

36:19.934 --> 36:21.638
Is there
a Good Guy doll around here?

36:21.671 --> 36:22.907
‐ A Good Guy what?

36:22.940 --> 36:25.445
‐ Chucky murdered
my whole family.

36:25.478 --> 36:28.952
‐ [shouting]

36:28.986 --> 36:32.259
‐ [screams]

36:32.292 --> 36:34.296
‐ Who's Chucky?

36:34.329 --> 36:35.666
‐ He framed me for the murders

36:35.700 --> 36:37.603
and put me
in a mental hospital.

36:41.778 --> 36:43.281
[gavel bangs]

36:43.314 --> 36:45.820
‐ I'm still alive!

36:45.853 --> 36:47.456
‐ I can honestly see that.

36:47.489 --> 36:50.563
‐ Two weeks ago, Chucky,

36:50.596 --> 36:52.700
he split his soul into pieces.

36:52.734 --> 36:56.742
‐ Ade boku Damballa.

36:56.775 --> 37:01.818
Give me all the power,
I beg of you!

37:01.852 --> 37:04.858
[dramatic music]

37:04.891 --> 37:08.331
‐ But one of those pieces
is inside me and I‐‐

37:08.364 --> 37:11.772
but I'm still here too.
‐ [grunting]

37:16.046 --> 37:17.349
‐ I can save you.

37:17.382 --> 37:18.685
I can fight him.

37:24.029 --> 37:26.333
[grunts]

37:26.367 --> 37:28.271
‐ Chucky!

37:28.304 --> 37:30.743
My stomach
is growling like a lion

37:30.776 --> 37:33.381
and this lion needs to eat.
‐ [groans]

37:33.414 --> 37:36.353
‐ And if you ever compare me
to my mother again,

37:36.387 --> 37:37.757
I will cut your heart out

37:37.790 --> 37:39.828
and feed it to a stranger.

37:41.898 --> 37:44.704
What are you doing
on the floor?

37:46.975 --> 37:49.814
‐ That was weird.
‐ What's going on?

37:52.653 --> 37:55.493
‐ [grunts, sighs]

37:55.526 --> 37:56.962
I dropped my knife.

37:56.995 --> 37:58.899
‐ Well, don't do it again.

37:58.932 --> 38:02.640
‐ You want to eat? Let's eat.

38:02.673 --> 38:04.511
Wet work for dessert.

38:04.544 --> 38:06.715
‐ My favorite.

38:16.635 --> 38:19.373
‐ Hey.

38:19.406 --> 38:23.414
Best if we keep this
Nica bullshit between us, huh?

38:23.447 --> 38:25.920
‐ [gurgling]

38:25.953 --> 38:30.028
‐ It'll be our little secret.
[chuckles]

38:44.891 --> 38:46.427
‐ Mrs. McGee, can't wait
for Rock the School Block. Hey, can we expect those famous

38:46.460 --> 38:49.032
everything but the sink cookies
this year?

38:49.066 --> 38:50.636
Great.

38:50.669 --> 38:52.940
Hey, Adrianna,
you ready to kick

38:52.974 --> 38:55.513
some Manchester butt
this Friday?

38:55.546 --> 38:56.648
Okay.

38:56.681 --> 39:00.488
Phyllis, so glad you made it.
Thank you.

39:00.523 --> 39:03.094
‐ Tommy ran away.
‐ He did?

39:03.127 --> 39:05.799
‐ I want Tommy back.
‐ Okay.

39:05.833 --> 39:08.404
I bet Tommy will be waiting
for you when you get home.

39:08.437 --> 39:09.774
‐ No, he won't!

39:12.513 --> 39:15.018
‐ You know, we could just
tell them about Chucky.

39:15.051 --> 39:16.120
Tell 'em he's dead.

39:16.153 --> 39:17.155
‐ My mom's not going
to believe that.

39:17.188 --> 39:19.494
‐ Nobody will believe us.

39:20.796 --> 39:22.332
‐ What‐‐what if they do?

39:23.936 --> 39:25.673
‐ Move.

39:31.016 --> 39:32.653
Lexy, what the hell?

39:37.496 --> 39:38.832
‐ Jake's doll Chucky was alive

39:38.865 --> 39:40.836
and he killed his dad,
and he killed Oliver,

39:40.869 --> 39:41.972
and the cop at the hospital,

39:42.005 --> 39:44.009
and your housekeeper too,
and he wouldn't stop killing,

39:44.042 --> 39:45.713
so we broke him into pieces
and now he's dead,

39:45.746 --> 39:48.619
so everyone can stop
worrying about it.

39:48.652 --> 39:50.889
You can stop worrying
about it too.

39:50.923 --> 39:53.595
‐ If you don't want to tell me
what's going on, fine,

39:53.629 --> 39:58.437
but making up stupid shit
like that is just embarrassing.

39:58.471 --> 40:00.809
Grow up, Lexy.

40:00.843 --> 40:01.811
Asshole.

40:05.753 --> 40:07.122
‐ Told you.

